President Obama and Vice President Biden met with faith leaders in the Oval Office to discuss the importance of passing immigration reform. The faith leaders expressed their concerns about the impact of the broken immigration system on families in their congregations. The President and the leaders discussed their shared commitment to raising awareness of the moral imperative for immigration reform and vowed to keep pressure on Congress to pass reform quickly. The President commended the faith leaders for their efforts in sharing their stories with Congress and called on House Republicans to take action on the bipartisan issue. The faith leaders thanked the President for his leadership and offered prayers for achieving the goals of immigration reform.